							<br class="clear"/>
							<!-- End each blog post -->
							
														
							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/richard-flanagan/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Screen-Shot-2016-03-29-at-12.45.52-PM-100x100.png" width="100" height="100" alt="Richard Flanagan" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/richard-flanagan/">Richard Flanagan</a></h6>
										Richard Flanagan is the author of six novels—<em>The Narrow Road to the Deep North</em> (for which he received the Man Booker Prize), <em>Death of a River Guide, The Sound of One Hand Clapping, Gould’s Book of Fish, The Unknown Terrorist,</em> and <em>Wanting</em>—which have received numerous honors and have been published in forty-two countries. He lives in Tasmania.																			</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
							</div>
